        "body" : "@conda-forge/staged-recipes, @conda-forge/core\r\n\r\nWhat is the guidance when vendoring patched versions of C libraries? \r\nIn the case of `rb-cool.io`, it vendors a [patched](https://github.com/tarcieri/cool.io/blob/0fd3fd1d8e8d81e24f79f809979367abc3f52b92/libev_ruby_gil.diff#L113-L145) version of `libev`  to solve an incompatibility between Ruby's global-interpreter-lock and libev's concurrency management. ",
